div class=\"fusion-section-separator-spacer-height\"></div></div></div><div class=\"fusion-section-separator section-separator hills-opacity fusion-section-separator-2 fusion-no-medium-visibility fusion-no-large-visibility\" style=\"--awb-spacer-padding-top:inherit;--awb-divider-height:75px;--awb-spacer-height:75px;--awb-sep-font-size:0;--awb-sep-line-height:0;\"><div class=\"fusion-section-separator-svg fusion-section-separator-fullwidth\"><svg class=\"fusion-hills-opacity-candy\" fill=\"rgba(0,65,83,1)\" preserveaspectratio=\"none\" version=\"1.1\" viewbox=\"0 -0.5 1024 182\" width=\"100%\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><path class=\"st0\" d=\"M0 182.086h1024V41.593c-28.058-21.504-60.109-37.581-97.075-37.581-112.845 0-198.144 93.798-289.792 93.798S437.658 6.777 351.846 6.777s-142.234 82.125-238.49 82.125c-63.078 0-75.776-31.744-113.357-53.658L0 182.086z\"></path>\n<path class=\"st1\" d=\"M1024 181.062v-75.878c-39.731 15.872-80.794 27.341-117.658 25.805-110.387-4.506-191.795-109.773-325.53-116.224-109.158-5.12-344.166 120.115-429.466 166.298H1024v-.001z\"></path>\n<path class=\"st2\" d=\"M0 182.086h1024V90.028C966.451 59.103 907.059 16.3 824.115 15.071 690.278 13.023 665.19 102.93 482.099 102.93S202.138-1.62 74.24.019C46.49.326 21.811 4.217 0 9.849v172.237z\"></path>\n<path class=\"st3\" d=\"M0 182.086h1024V80.505c-37.171 19.558-80.691 35.328-139.571 36.25-151.142 2.355-141.619-28.57-298.496-29.184s-138.854 47.002-305.459 43.725C132.813 128.428 91.238 44.563 0 28.179v153.907z\"></path>\n<path class=\"st4\" d=\"M0 182.086h1024v-77.312c-49.05 20.07-120.525 42.394-193.229 42.086-128.922-.512-159.846-72.294-255.795-72.294-89.088 0-134.656 80.179-245.043 82.022S169.063 99.346 49.971 97.401C32.768 97.094 16.077 99.244 0 103.135v78.951z\"></path>\n</svg></div><div class=\"fusion-section-separator-spacer fusion-section-separator-fullwidth\"><div class=\"fusion-section-separator-spacer-height\"></div></div></div></div></div>\n</div></div>\n</div>",
  "markdown": "[![](/images/final_MarineLife_2030_v2-1-e1671565154817.png)](https://marinelife2030.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/final_MarineLife_2030_v2.pdf)\n\n![](/images/TriColorWave.png)\n\nMarine Life 2030 is implemented utilizing a bottom-up approach which relies on volunteers from all around the world. A series of learning communities have been established, focused on:\n\n  * __\n\nBest Practices and Interoperability\n\n  * __\n\nCo-design and Stakeholder Engagement\n\n  * __\n\nCapacity Development Citizen Science\n\n  * __\n\nEarly Career Ocean Professionals (ECOPS)\n\n  * __\n\nExternal Communications and Outreach\n\n  * __\n\nIndigenous Knowledge\n\n\n\n\n  * __\n\nBest Practices and Interoperability\n\n  * __\n\nCo-design and Stakeholder Engagement\n\n  * __\n\nCapacity Development Citizen Science\n\n  * __\n\nEarly Career Ocean Professionals (ECOPS)\n\n  * __\n\nExternal Communications and Outreach\n\n  * __\n\nIndigenous Knowledge\n\n\n\n\nMore information about the program is available [here](https://drive.google.com/file/d/13CszfRpt91_kLflGsjyEJblCeLjTiA96/view) and [here](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1eRC0v1manpQoSgcKphfNycFIVg1GYCJz/view).\n\nIf you are interested in affiliation with Marine Life 2030, please seek endorsement by the UN Ocean Decade requesting such affiliation (visit the UN Ocean Decade [website](https://forum.oceandecade.org/page/take-action) to learn more). Please also review the Principles and Criteria for Marine Life 2030-affiliated Projects and Partners [here](https://marinelife2030.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/ML2030-Principles-Criteria-for-Projects-and-Partners.docx.pdf).\n\nThe Marine Biodiversity Observation Network (MBON) calls on nations, scientists, sponsors, and stakeholders to work together as a community of practice to support Marine Life 2030 to enable a dialogue, and coordination and cooperation between programmes. Please see this [Dear Colleague Letter](https://marinelife2030.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Dear-Colleague-Letter.pdf) and join the MBON/Marine Life 2030 Community of Practice ([GEO BON Members](https://members.geobon.org/pages/index)).\n\nEmail us at [email protected] with questions or for more information.\n\n_We encourage you to download the above graphic and use it in your working sessions related to Marine Life 2030. If you use it, please consider sharing it on social media using the hashtag #MarineLife2030!_",
